fields.description: The type of authentication method used to perform this step of authentication. Possible values: Password, SMS, Voice, Authenticator App, Software OATH token, Satisfied by token, Previously satisfied.
fields.name: AuthenticationMethod

fields.description: Details about the authentication method used to perform this authentication step. For example, phone number (for SMS and voice), device name (for Authenticator app), and password source (for example, cloud, AD FS, PTA, PHS).
fields.name: AuthenticationMethodDetail

fields.description: Represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z.
fields.name: AuthenticationStepDateTime

fields.description: The step of authentication that this satisfied. For example, primary authentication, or multifactor authentication.
fields.name: AuthenticationStepRequirement

fields.description: Details about why the step succeeded or failed. For examples, user is blocked, fraud code entered, no phone input - timed out, phone unreachable, or claim in token.
fields.name: AuthenticationStepResultDetail

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: Indicates the status of the authentication step. Possible values: succeeded, failed.
fields.name: Succeeded
